The paper deals with the problem of adversarial robustness and generalization in deep networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on training strategies and experiments on image datasets, it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, since the paper deals with the security aspect of deep learning, it could also belong to the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
